/user/data get put patch delete

Entity representing a datum

get

Get the datum. The user data field is an arbitrary object where developers can put custom data associated with a specific user. N.B. This data will be shared over all projects and apps in a deployment, consider indexing project/app specific data.

put

Add a new datum to WebGME. Overwrites the data field.

patch

Update datum within WebGME. Updates/overwrites the user's data with the sent values for matching keys.

delete

Delete datum from WebGME. Clears out the user's data field (sets it to empty dictionary).

get /user/data

Get the datum. The user data field is an arbitrary object where developers can put custom data associated with a specific user. N.B. This data will be shared over all projects and apps in a deployment, consider indexing project/app specific data.

  • Response

HTTP status code 200

Body

Type: application/json

Example:

{
  "pluingSettings": {
    "MyPlugin1": {
      "enable": true,
      "save": false
    },
    "MyPlugin2": {
      "outputName": "afile.ext"
    }
  }
}

HTTP status code 404

Body

Type: application/json

Example:

{"message": "datum not found" }

/users/{username} get put patch delete

Entity representing a user

get

Get the user.

put

Add a new user to WebGME. Requires user.siteAdmin.

patch

Update user within WebGME. Requires user.siteAdmin if setting siteAdmin.

delete

Delete user from WebGME. Requires is current user or user.siteAdmin.

get /users/{username}

Get the user.

  • Request
  • Response

URI Parameters

  • username: required (string)

HTTP status code 200

Body

Type: application/json

Example:

{
  "_id":"demo",
  "email":"demo@mail.com",
  "canCreate":true,
  "projects":{
    "guest+aaaaaa":{
      "read":true,
      "write":true,
      "delete":false
    },
    "demo+ASDF":{
      "read":true,
      "write":true,
      "delete":true
    }
  },
  "orgs":[
    "ATeam"
  ],
  "siteAdmin":false,
  "data": {}
}

HTTP status code 404

Body

Type: application/json

Example:

{"message": "user not found" }

/projects/{ownerId}/{projectName} get put patch delete

Entity representing a project

get

Get the project. Requires read access for project.

put

Add a new project to WebGME. Requires user.canCreate.

patch

Update project within WebGME. Requires write access for project.

delete

Delete project from WebGME. Requires delete access for project.

get /projects/{ownerId}/{projectName}

Get the project. Requires read access for project.

  • Request
  • Response

URI Parameters

  • ownerId: required (string)

    Example:

    guest
  • projectName: required (string)

    Example:

    ActivePanels

HTTP status code 200

Body

Type: application/json

Example:

{
  "_id": "demo+FSM",

  "name": "FSM",

/projects/{ownerId}/{projectName}/authorize/{userOrOrgId} delete

delete

Remove user's or organization's access rights to the project. Requires at least one of the following from user; is owner of the project, is admin in the organization that owns the project, or is siteAdmin.

delete /projects/{ownerId}/{projectName}/authorize/{userOrOrgId}

Remove user's or organization's access rights to the project. Requires at least one of the following from user; is owner of the project, is admin in the organization that owns the project, or is siteAdmin.

  • Request
  • Response

URI Parameters

  • ownerId: required (string)

    Example:

    guest
  • projectName: required (string)

    Example:

    ActivePanels
  • userOrOrgId: required (string)

    Example:

    demoUser

HTTP status code 204

HTTP status code 403

HTTP status code 404

/projects/{ownerId}/{projectName}/authorize/{userOrOrgId}/{rights} put

put

Grants user or organization access to the project. Requires at least one of the following from user; is owner of the project, is admin in the organization that owns the project, or is siteAdmin.

put /projects/{ownerId}/{projectName}/authorize/{userOrOrgId}/{rights}

Grants user or organization access to the project. Requires at least one of the following from user; is owner of the project, is admin in the organization that owns the project, or is siteAdmin.

  • Request
  • Response

URI Parameters

  • ownerId: required (string)

    Example:

    guest
  • projectName: required (string)

    Example:

    ActivePanels
  • userOrOrgId: required (string)

    Example:

    demoUser
  • rights: required (string)

    Combination of r-read, w-write, d-delete

    Example:

    rwd

HTTP status code 204

HTTP status code 403

HTTP status code 404

/projects/{ownerId}/{projectName}/commits get

get

Retrives an array of latested commits made to the project. Requires read access for project.

get /projects/{ownerId}/{projectName}/commits

Retrives an array of latested commits made to the project. Requires read access for project.

  • Request
  • Response

URI Parameters

  • ownerId: required (string)

    Example:

    guest
  • projectName: required (string)

    Example:

    ActivePanels

Query Parameters

  • n: (number)

    Maximum number of commits to retrieve (default 100).

    Example:

    2
